Crypto trading

Unlike traditional stock markets, cryptocurrency trading never stops, making it virtually impossible for private traders to:
    Track market fluctuations
    Diversify risk 
    Reduce error and ensure trading discipline 24 hours a day, 7 days a week, 365 days a year

Some estimates suggest that around half of internet traffic is made up of bots that interact with web pages and users, scan for content, and perform other tasks.

Trading bots work in three essential stages: signal generator, risk allocation and execution.

Many reports suggest that around 80% of trading on the stock market is done via algorithmic-based automated programs.

Emotionless trading

Higher trading speed

Backtesting and paper trading

Trading bots are about minimizing risk by not putting all of your eggs in one basket.
    One way to diversify your risk is to run multiple trading bots.

